v2.1.1: trainers as entities + gym hours simplified + faster sync

Trainers are now first-class entities with their own weekly schedule.
The gym opening hours config is decoupled from trainer assignments,
which makes both clearer and lets the mobile app derive "who is on
duty" automatically per slot.

New "Entrenadores" section:
- Full CRUD: add, edit, color-code, activate/deactivate, delete
- Per-trainer weekly schedule editor (multiple slots per day allowed)
- Sidebar nav entry below "Clases"
- New cloud_trainers + cloud_trainer_schedules tables with RLS so
  mobile clients can read their gym's trainers

Gym hours modal simplified:
- Removed the confusing per-shift trainer entry
- Back to days + opening hours per day (Mon 07:00-22:00, etc.)
- Info banner directs to the Entrenadores section
- "Visible en app movil" toggle to hide the gym schedule for clients
- Save now allowed without shifts when toggle is OFF

Faster end-to-end sync:
- Critical mutations (classes/trainers/customers/payments) debounce
  drops from 3s to 1s
- Mobile useClasses now polls every 20s + refetches on tab focus
- Worst case propagation: ~22s (was effectively never without
  manual pull-to-refresh)

UI cleanups:
- "Gimnasio" class hidden from Class management list (canonical
  source of gym hours is the dedicated tab + modal)
- Weekly schedule accordion excludes Gimnasio slots from the
  class schedule overview
- setGymHours auto-consolidates duplicate "Gimnasio" rows, preferring
  the one that already has shift data

